-- Sell Aussie as China Slowdown May Drop It to 84 U.S. Cents, Westpac Says
-- Candice Zachariahs
-- 2010-06-28T05:45:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/sell-aussie-as-china-slowdown-may-drop-it-to-84-u-s-cents-westpac-says.html

          
          
             Investors may benefit from selling
the Australian dollar against the greenback as it may decline 4
percent as Chinaâ€™s economy slows, Westpac Banking Corp. said.  
 Investors should sell the so-called Aussie as it gains
toward 88.15 cents, looking for it to drop initially to 84
cents, the Sydney-based bank said today in an e-mailed note to
clients. They should exit the trade if the Australian dollar
rises above 89 cents, it said. The currency traded at 87.51 U.S.
cents as of 3:40 p.m. in Sydney.  
